WEBVTT

00:20.754 --> 00:23.891
- That'll do.

00:29.197 --> 00:31.365
Good job, kid.
- Thank you.

00:31.865 --> 00:33.334
- All right.

00:33.934 --> 00:35.903
Here you go.

00:39.907 --> 00:41.609
You know where to go?
- Yes, sir.

00:41.609 --> 00:43.344
- Get to it.

00:47.848 --> 00:49.650
- This is never what I wanted.

00:49.650 --> 00:51.619
Never where I thought I'd be.

00:52.486 --> 00:54.922
But then I'd never been
anywhere else.

00:56.290 --> 00:59.393
A little further,
past that tree.

00:59.793 --> 01:02.596
Even when they sent me away,

01:02.596 --> 01:04.632
they just sent me
right back here.

01:27.121 --> 01:29.457
- Every member of my family
fights this fight

01:29.457 --> 01:30.891
in one way or another.

01:30.891 --> 01:34.162
And so does every family
who calls Kingstown home.

01:34.762 --> 01:37.665
So do a lot of families
who will never call it home,

01:37.665 --> 01:39.900
but they live here anyway.

01:39.900 --> 01:42.603
Waiting.
Always waiting.

01:42.603 --> 01:44.738
- You drop somethin'?

01:45.173 --> 01:48.509
- Now it's up to me to keep
the rats in the cage content.

01:49.943 --> 01:53.181
And the keepers
from becoming rats, themselves.

02:05.092 --> 02:06.960
- This is a company town

02:06.960 --> 02:09.697
and the business
is incarceration.

02:09.697 --> 02:12.833
Seven prisons
in a 10-mile radius.

02:12.833 --> 02:16.937
20,000 lost souls
with no hope, no future.

02:18.472 --> 02:22.276
And I'm their link to a world
that doesn't want them.

02:22.876 --> 02:24.512
I'm the life raft.

02:26.714 --> 02:28.616
I'm the mayor of Kingstown.

03:33.781 --> 03:36.083
- Now he's got all these
fucking guards hangin' out

03:36.083 --> 03:38.552
around his cell like a bunch
of fuckin' vultures.

03:38.552 --> 03:41.221
I told you last week
to get him fuckin' transferred.

03:41.221 --> 03:43.624
- Do I look like
the warden to you?

03:43.624 --> 03:45.225
He hit a fuckin' guard.

03:45.225 --> 03:47.094
- So help me, if any
of these bastards punks my kid-

03:47.094 --> 03:49.096
- You'll what?

03:49.096 --> 03:51.332
What are you gonna do, Walter?

03:51.765 --> 03:53.200
Huh?
Just 'cause you pay us,

03:53.200 --> 03:54.902
you think you can
talk to him like that?

03:54.902 --> 03:56.537
Is that it?

03:56.537 --> 03:58.539
Who the fuck do ya think
you're talkin' to?

04:00.608 --> 04:03.611
- The mayor.
- Yeah, you're fuckin' right.

04:03.611 --> 04:05.145
- I'm sorry.

04:05.145 --> 04:06.880
- Look, we had your kid
in protection, right?

04:06.880 --> 04:09.116
But he's got a big fuckin' mouth
and not much common sense,

04:09.116 --> 04:10.150
so what do you want?

04:10.150 --> 04:11.585
- He's in Ad Seg.

04:11.585 --> 04:13.086
Believe me, that's
the safest place he can be.

04:13.086 --> 04:15.456
Your kid fractured
that guard's jaw.

04:15.456 --> 04:17.224
But when they
throw the book at him,

04:17.224 --> 04:19.360
they don't want some
beat-to-shit 17-year-old

04:19.360 --> 04:22.129
in front of that judge,
so, he's fine for now.

04:22.129 --> 04:24.064
But he's gotta understand
and you've gotta understand,

04:24.064 --> 04:26.133
he's gettin' another five years
on that sentence.

04:26.133 --> 04:27.501
And he's gotta come to grips
with the fact

04:27.501 --> 04:29.036
that his only protection
is with the whites,

04:29.036 --> 04:30.671
and he's gonna
have to play ball to get it.

04:30.671 --> 04:32.239
And that means
he keeps his mouth shut

04:32.239 --> 04:34.274
and he does
what he's supposed to do.

04:34.274 --> 04:36.043
Because if he doesn't,
he's gonna end up

04:36.043 --> 04:38.011
somebody's girl
for the next decade.

04:38.011 --> 04:40.047
Be sure to
make that clear to him.

04:40.047 --> 04:42.483
- Sorry. He's my son.

04:42.483 --> 04:44.251
- Well, maybe next time
don't have him cookin' up meth

04:44.251 --> 04:47.621
in the Caraway campground.
How 'bout that?

04:47.621 --> 04:48.889
- Look, tell you what.

04:48.889 --> 04:50.123
You tell him to rope a sheet.

04:50.123 --> 04:51.359
If it looks like
they're gonna punk him,

04:51.359 --> 04:53.160
you have him noose up
before bed check.

04:53.160 --> 04:54.395
They'll put him
on suicide watch.

04:54.395 --> 04:57.097
It'll keep him
on the warden's radar.

04:57.931 --> 05:00.233
- Okay.
- Let's go.

05:07.741 --> 05:09.510
Jackass.

05:10.243 --> 05:11.379
We got a meet
at the Carriage House.

05:11.379 --> 05:13.146
You wanna bring this up?

05:13.146 --> 05:14.582
- That kid's gotten
all the fuckin' help

05:14.582 --> 05:16.083
we're gonna give him.
- Good.

05:19.920 --> 05:21.254
- Yep?
- Is there anyone out there

05:21.254 --> 05:22.890
with somethin'
I gotta hear right now?

05:22.890 --> 05:24.392
- No more than usual.
- Good.

05:24.392 --> 05:26.894
Then we're gonna
be back in an hour.

05:27.227 --> 05:30.531
- Oh wait, um,
remember Milo Center?

05:30.531 --> 05:32.065
His wife's here.

05:32.065 --> 05:34.835
- What does she want?
- Wouldn't tell me.

05:34.835 --> 05:36.704
- All right.

05:38.939 --> 05:40.207
You go on,
I'll see what this is.

05:40.207 --> 05:41.475
- You sure?

05:41.475 --> 05:43.844
- Yeah, if she's here
Milo sent her.

05:44.277 --> 05:46.246
- Okay.

05:56.156 --> 05:58.225
- Vera.
- Mitch.

05:58.225 --> 06:02.463
- How's Milo?
- Good. Ya know, counting.

06:03.497 --> 06:05.633
- It's a little early for that.

06:05.633 --> 06:07.435
- He's an optimist.

06:08.436 --> 06:11.772
- Well, tell me.
What can I do for him?

06:11.772 --> 06:14.274
- He needs something moved.
Could you close that?

06:17.177 --> 06:18.512
- No one can hear us out there.

06:18.512 --> 06:21.482
- I don't mind the smoke.
Please.

06:31.892 --> 06:33.527
- All right.

06:33.527 --> 06:35.529
- I leave for Estonia
tomorrow night

06:35.529 --> 06:38.799
and I must take it with me.
- It?

06:38.799 --> 06:40.801
Well, I gotta know
what I'm pickin' up.

06:40.801 --> 06:43.270
- From that thing.

06:43.771 --> 06:45.372
You know.

06:45.806 --> 06:49.342
- All of it?
- He said 10,000 for you.

06:51.779 --> 06:54.281
- This is a little outside
of what we do.

06:54.281 --> 06:56.349
I'm gonna have to hear
from Milo.

06:56.349 --> 06:58.085
Make sure that you're not
cookin' this up yourself.

06:58.085 --> 06:59.252
No offense.

06:59.252 --> 07:01.622
- He said
he could call after 3:00.

07:01.622 --> 07:03.891
- Have you got the where
and all that?

07:11.231 --> 07:13.300
Oh, a map.

07:13.300 --> 07:14.635
Is there gonna be
an X on the ground?

07:14.635 --> 07:16.970
Or maybe he has
a GPS coordinate, or-

07:16.970 --> 07:19.439
- Milo said no electronics.

07:19.439 --> 07:23.376
He would like you to make a copy
and I keep this one.

07:42.963 --> 07:46.600
- Thank you.
This is far.

07:47.000 --> 07:48.569
- County took the land.

07:48.569 --> 07:51.204
They will auction it off
next month.

07:51.204 --> 07:54.842
- Is there anyone out there?
- Milo said no.

07:55.375 --> 07:57.845
- All right.
We'll get it tonight.

07:57.845 --> 07:59.613
- Thank you.

07:59.613 --> 08:02.750
So tomorrow?

08:05.118 --> 08:06.987
Thanks, Mitch.

08:16.864 --> 08:20.000
- Damn, there's some fine-ass
women in this motherfucker.

08:35.482 --> 08:38.451
- This place, 20,000 inmates

08:38.451 --> 08:41.254
and 40,000 people
to babysit them,

08:41.254 --> 08:44.725
feed them, teach them.

08:44.725 --> 08:46.827
And when they get out,
employ them

08:46.827 --> 08:50.731
or convince them to leave
'cause this place is full.

08:55.135 --> 08:57.304
- Oh, hi honey.
- Any for me?

08:57.304 --> 08:59.907
- Big booth.
- Okay, thanks.

09:01.141 --> 09:02.409
- I'm not takin'
this shit any more.

09:02.409 --> 09:04.077
You show up
and do your fuckin' job.

09:04.077 --> 09:05.512
- Hey.
- Hey man, what's up?

09:05.512 --> 09:07.815
- How are ya?
- Good to see ya buddy.

09:07.815 --> 09:09.549
- I need coffee.

09:10.117 --> 09:11.985
Thanks, I'm dyin' here.

09:13.320 --> 09:15.488
Thank you.

09:15.488 --> 09:18.225
I saw um, I saw your ex
the other day.

09:18.225 --> 09:19.760
- Oh f--
If there was any justice,

09:19.760 --> 09:22.162
she was ridin' the brass pole
at the Elephant, please tell me.

09:22.162 --> 09:23.396
- Nah, man,
Agnes does not

09:23.396 --> 09:24.832
have the temperament
to be strippin'.

09:26.366 --> 09:27.935
- She was with that douchebag

09:27.935 --> 09:29.603
from the public defender's
office, that prick.

09:29.603 --> 09:31.304
- Oh God, I hope she marries
that fuck soon.

09:31.304 --> 09:34.507
- Yeah, she thought
you had no money.

09:34.507 --> 09:36.143
- Hey, you gonna deal with
both of my family functions.

09:36.143 --> 09:38.679
- No, no, that's you.
- Not me, no, no, no, nope.

09:38.679 --> 09:40.247
- All right, what do we got?
Jim?

09:40.247 --> 09:43.250
- Um, my fuckin' family.
- Uh-huh.

09:43.250 --> 09:46.186
- My nephew, Sam.
- What? He just started.

09:46.186 --> 09:47.520
- Mm-hmm.
- Three months ago?

09:47.520 --> 09:50.357
- And they got him pretty good.
- Who?

09:50.357 --> 09:52.259
- The blacks.
- How?

09:52.259 --> 09:54.461
- I don't know.
Somethin' about

09:54.461 --> 09:56.529
one of them
always joking with him,

09:56.529 --> 10:00.634
buddying up, asking him
to mail a letter home.

10:00.634 --> 10:03.370
Some other bullshit about
another guard blockin' his mail.

10:03.370 --> 10:05.873
He did it.
- What a cherry.

10:05.873 --> 10:08.308
Geez, didn't you prep him
any better than this?

10:08.308 --> 10:10.543
- But he's fuckin' 22, Mike.

10:10.543 --> 10:13.613
He thinks these pieces of shit
are his brothers.

10:13.613 --> 10:16.149
These kids, they don't,
they don't get it, man.

10:16.149 --> 10:17.550
They just, they don't see it.

10:17.550 --> 10:19.219
- Yeah, well,
they fuckin' got him now.

10:19.219 --> 10:22.856
Okay?
- Yeah.

10:26.126 --> 10:28.395
Who's the inmate?

10:28.395 --> 10:30.864
- This piece of shit.

10:32.766 --> 10:35.969
- He got a gang outside?
- Yeah, he's Crip.

10:37.905 --> 10:41.074
- Okay, well, there ya go.
That's good news, right?

10:41.374 --> 10:43.310
There's always
this sanction thing.

10:43.643 --> 10:45.578
We're fine, right?
And the inmate's

10:45.578 --> 10:48.048
not tryin' to put your nephew
in his pocket, right?

10:48.048 --> 10:49.516
You know, all right, look.

10:49.516 --> 10:52.219
If your nephew sent a letter
to any guy in the juice,

10:52.219 --> 10:53.553
then I'll get the thing back.

10:53.553 --> 10:55.188
But we're gonna have
to make a trade for it.

10:55.188 --> 10:57.224
So is swing shift
the best time to launch a ball?

10:57.224 --> 10:59.226
- Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
- And look, everybody's onboard.

10:59.226 --> 11:02.129
All right, it's not like we all,
we all haven't been there.

11:02.129 --> 11:04.898
- Just make sure there's no
Rambos in the turrets, okay?

11:04.898 --> 11:06.199
If I get this letter,
they're gonna pick

11:06.199 --> 11:08.836
the day and the time.
So, we got to be ready.

11:08.836 --> 11:10.871
For somethin' like this,
I'm sure it's gonna be tarred.

11:10.871 --> 11:12.706
Just make sure we have
our people in the yard.

11:12.706 --> 11:14.942
Okay? No fuckin' subs.
- It's not a problem.

11:14.942 --> 11:17.410
Our whole fuckin' unit
runs the place, except SIS.

11:17.410 --> 11:18.678
It's fine, Mike.

11:18.678 --> 11:20.147
- I don't want any sweeps,
none of that shit

11:20.147 --> 11:22.850
'cause I gotta let everybody
know of this, all right?

11:23.951 --> 11:27.087
Your nephew, gonna have a target
on his back for a while.

11:28.956 --> 11:31.524
- Once we get this handled,
we'll put him up in a tower.

11:31.524 --> 11:32.760
Okay? He'll be fine.

11:32.760 --> 11:34.127
- Yeah, well,
I don't know about that

11:34.127 --> 11:35.462
because he'll probably wanna
start shootin' people

11:35.462 --> 11:37.630
left, right and center.

11:37.630 --> 11:40.467
- As long as he shoots
the right fool.

11:40.467 --> 11:43.804
- Hey, I'll handle it.

11:44.404 --> 11:45.472
Okay?
- Yeah.

11:45.472 --> 11:46.639
- Let's go.
- Thanks, Mike.

11:46.639 --> 11:47.941
Best to the mayor, all right?
- Yeah.

11:47.941 --> 11:51.544
- Hey Mike,
is this gonna cost him with you?

11:52.946 --> 11:54.882
- Absolutely.

12:06.593 --> 12:09.362
- Well, even today,
the textbooks will teach you

12:09.362 --> 12:11.765
that it was a war
over state's rights.

12:11.765 --> 12:14.567
The result is the same.
And it was.

12:14.567 --> 12:17.404
It was a war
over state's rights.

12:17.404 --> 12:19.672
It was over
a state's right to decide

12:19.672 --> 12:22.209
its own position on slavery.

12:22.209 --> 12:24.778
So, this was a war

12:24.778 --> 12:29.549
fought for the freedom
to choose slavery.

12:29.883 --> 12:32.786
And the only time
in recorded history

12:32.786 --> 12:35.622
that the oppressors
fought each other

12:35.622 --> 12:38.725
over the rights
of the oppressed.

12:39.126 --> 12:43.730
It was the most formative event
in this nation's history.

12:44.531 --> 12:47.367
But the catharsis
of that union victory

12:47.367 --> 12:51.571
and the freedom of the slaves,
it was short lived.

12:51.571 --> 12:54.674
A decade later,
a new Union army

12:54.674 --> 12:58.145
made up of mostly
imprisoned Confederate soldiers

12:58.145 --> 13:01.614
and immigrants
reignited the genocide

13:01.614 --> 13:05.485
begun by Columbus
some 400 years earlier.

13:05.886 --> 13:08.021
There's a wonderful-

13:08.021 --> 13:10.490
- Okay, read the first two
chapters.

13:10.490 --> 13:12.359
I'll see you all tomorrow.

13:12.359 --> 13:13.793
- All right, ladies.
Take your books.

13:13.793 --> 13:16.263
Leave your pencils.
We'll start here.

13:27.007 --> 13:30.443
- My grandparents
are from Pine Ridge.

13:30.443 --> 13:32.812
That's where I was raised.

13:32.812 --> 13:35.515
- You're a long way from home.

13:35.748 --> 13:38.151
Do you know this?
- No.

13:38.952 --> 13:40.287
- Well, it might speak to you.

13:40.287 --> 13:42.455
It's about how your family
came to live on Pine Ridge

13:42.455 --> 13:44.724
in the first place.

13:45.425 --> 13:48.528
- Um, I was wondering.

13:48.528 --> 13:50.163
I got a cousin coming here

13:50.163 --> 13:54.601
and I was hoping
you'd ask the mayor.

13:54.601 --> 13:58.505
I don't have any money,
but it's nothing.

13:58.505 --> 14:00.773
If I hadn't
gotten written up for-

14:00.773 --> 14:04.644
- Don't ever, ever,

14:06.246 --> 14:09.049
mention my sons to me again.

14:10.317 --> 14:12.652
Is that clear?

14:12.652 --> 14:14.387
- I didn't mean
to be disrespectful.

14:14.387 --> 14:17.024
- Get the fuck outta here.

14:42.515 --> 14:44.784
- Yeah.
- All right, what happened?

14:44.784 --> 14:47.287
- It's a problem.
- How big a problem?

14:47.287 --> 14:49.022
- Like a seven.

14:49.022 --> 14:50.757
- You gotta start on it
right now?

14:50.757 --> 14:52.325
- Uh, well, I should.

14:52.325 --> 14:55.095
- You near the lake?
- Yeah, I'm passing it.

14:55.095 --> 14:57.664
- Good, so am I.
Meet me at the beach.

15:04.871 --> 15:08.475
- Milo buried his take
on some land north of here.

15:08.475 --> 15:10.510
We gotta go get it.

15:10.510 --> 15:12.579
- Great.

15:12.579 --> 15:15.382
- It's a hassle, but it's worth
10 for our trouble.

15:16.984 --> 15:20.220
- Yeah.
Gonna need Kyle.

15:20.587 --> 15:23.456
- He's not on duty.
- Tell him to pick up a shift.

15:27.927 --> 15:30.697
- How was Ed?

15:31.098 --> 15:33.466
- Tim Weaver's nephew
got hooked.

15:33.466 --> 15:35.668
Mailed a letter
to some low-level Crip.

15:35.668 --> 15:37.904
I don't know
if it was sanctioned.

15:44.077 --> 15:46.479
- Fuckin' Mondays.

15:48.115 --> 15:51.018
Fuckin' Mondays.

15:52.319 --> 15:55.255
Fuck it, get in the car.
Let's go see Bunny.

15:55.255 --> 15:56.656
- All right.

16:25.118 --> 16:26.319
- Why are y'all
dressed like cops?

16:26.319 --> 16:27.554
- Why are you dressed

16:27.554 --> 16:29.256
like you're mannin'
a weather station?

16:29.256 --> 16:31.824
- You're a funny motherfucker,
Mitch.

16:31.824 --> 16:33.826
- It is hot as hell up in here
for October though, right?

16:33.826 --> 16:35.528
- Take your parka off.
Enjoy autumn, fuck.

16:35.528 --> 16:37.030
- What the fuck
you want me to do?

16:37.030 --> 16:38.198
Sit behind a desk?
Nah-uh,

16:38.198 --> 16:40.233
this coat holds all of my shit.

16:40.233 --> 16:42.402
- Can we get five minutes
with you?

16:42.402 --> 16:44.104
- You,
go chill by the front door.

16:44.104 --> 16:47.874
You, go get me a uh, a snowcone.

16:47.874 --> 16:49.442
- Where I gonna
find you a snowcone?

16:49.442 --> 16:51.578
- The 7-11, fool.
- That's a Slurpie.

16:51.578 --> 16:53.680
You gotta get a snowcone
from a snowcone truck.

16:53.680 --> 16:55.915
I could get you a Blizzard.
Got them Blizzards at the Q.

16:55.915 --> 16:57.650
- Yeah, you are dressed
for a blizzard.

16:57.650 --> 16:59.619
- Motherfucker, go get me
some cold, frozen shit.

16:59.619 --> 17:01.621
I don't care where it from,
aight?

17:01.621 --> 17:04.524
- Aight.
- Fruit flavored.

17:05.892 --> 17:09.596
I'm sorry, do I speak Spanish
or some shit like that?

17:09.596 --> 17:11.598
Damn.

17:11.598 --> 17:13.266
What y'all doin' down here?

17:13.266 --> 17:14.634
- Well, one of your guys,
he hooked a guard.

17:14.634 --> 17:16.002
Clean kid, real green.

17:16.002 --> 17:18.271
- Yeah, yeah, yeah,
my boy got that letter.

17:18.271 --> 17:20.673
So, what, y'all wanna trade?
- Sure.

17:20.673 --> 17:22.842
- What you got?
I mean, I fish a good catch.

17:22.842 --> 17:24.877
They, they can milk
that fool forever.

17:24.877 --> 17:27.914
- Ah, it's Tim Weaver's nephew,
so, it's not gonna go that far.

17:27.914 --> 17:30.450
- Cold motherfucker,
I outta trick his nephew out.

17:30.450 --> 17:32.585
- Yeah, if you wanna
get your son shot in the yard.

17:32.585 --> 17:35.855
- True dat, true dat.
True dat shit.

17:36.656 --> 17:39.726
Okay, just the FedEX then.

17:39.726 --> 17:42.862
But I gotta move some product,
so get me a kilo over.

17:42.862 --> 17:45.031
- FedEx is only two ounces,
Bunny.

17:45.031 --> 17:46.766
- Y'all 'bout to be
some tennis ball hittin'

17:46.766 --> 17:48.201
motherfuckers, man.
Come on.

17:48.201 --> 17:49.869
- Shit, come on.
This helps you out

17:49.869 --> 17:51.504
as much as anyone. I mean,
Tim's wired pretty tight.

17:51.504 --> 17:53.573
Everyone's on his side.
This is free money for you.

17:53.573 --> 17:55.542
It was a good catch. Your guy
just picked the wrong kid.

17:55.542 --> 17:58.278
I'm just here to warn you,
but come on.

