43:29.775 --> 43:31.609
But we never
fuckin' break a deal.

43:31.609 --> 43:35.113
Do you understand?
Never with anybody, ever.

43:35.113 --> 43:36.447
- Aight, aight, aight.

43:36.447 --> 43:38.383
We're just a little worked up.
That's all.

43:38.383 --> 43:43.354
That's all, man, okay?
- Yeah, ya think?

43:44.690 --> 43:48.193
What the fuck?
Maybe fuckin' decaf next time.

43:48.193 --> 43:50.461
I'll talk to Mitch and see
what the fuck went south.

43:50.461 --> 43:52.530
And we'll fix it.
But look at me.

43:52.530 --> 43:54.299
The only way
this shit works for anyone

43:54.299 --> 43:57.268
is if everyone trusts us.

43:57.268 --> 43:59.971
That way we can trust you, okay?

43:59.971 --> 44:01.239
- Aight, aight.

44:01.239 --> 44:02.507
- Don't point a gun at me,
motherfucker.

44:02.507 --> 44:04.609
- I got you, man.
I'm just a little worked up.

44:04.609 --> 44:07.112
- Yeah, I hear you.
- He's dyin' up in there.

44:07.112 --> 44:09.247
He's leavin' that place
in a box, Mike.

44:09.247 --> 44:12.417
A fuckin' box.
That's my fuckin' cousin, Mike.

44:12.417 --> 44:15.687
- Everyone's someone's
fuckin' cousin in this town.

44:16.221 --> 44:18.757
- He took my fuckin' gun.
- Go get it, he's right there.

44:20.992 --> 44:23.161
There he go, go get it.

44:24.996 --> 44:28.266
- OPERATOR: You've reached the
voice mailbox of Mitch McLusky.

44:28.266 --> 44:29.801
Please leave a message.

44:29.801 --> 44:31.903
- Mitch, you fuckin'
son of a bitch, where are you?

44:31.903 --> 44:33.471
Where the fuck are you?
Where are you?

44:33.471 --> 44:35.040
Is this what
you wanted to tell me, huh?

44:35.040 --> 44:36.641
What the fuck happened?

44:36.641 --> 44:39.577
Those maniacs just tried
to fuckin' kill me, Mitch.

44:39.577 --> 44:41.546
Ya know, gettin' this letter's
gonna be a fuckin' lot of work.

44:41.546 --> 44:44.449
You know that?
Pick up your fuckin' phone.

44:44.449 --> 44:46.117
Fuck!

44:51.189 --> 44:52.791
What the fuck?

44:54.893 --> 44:56.661
Shit.

44:57.195 --> 44:59.197
What the hell?

45:04.903 --> 45:06.437
What?

45:06.437 --> 45:08.439
- Mike, just jump into my car
here, let me talk to ya.

45:08.439 --> 45:10.441
- What happened?
- Let me just talk to ya.

45:10.441 --> 45:12.343
Mike, you don't wanna see this.
- The fuck I don't.

45:12.343 --> 45:15.313
- Mike, slow down
let me talk to you.

45:15.713 --> 45:17.215
Come on.

45:20.986 --> 45:23.088
- How?

45:24.189 --> 45:26.557
- A gunshot back of the head,
Mike, it was real quick.

45:26.557 --> 45:28.626
Mike, Mike, come on.

45:28.626 --> 45:30.428
- RADIO: One, David, one, zero,
nine, nine, nine, six.

45:33.098 --> 45:36.467
- You're all right.
Mike, look.

45:38.536 --> 45:39.771
- What the fuck?

45:39.771 --> 45:41.672
- Vera Center was found dead
in her house last night.

45:41.672 --> 45:43.041
She was raped, strangled

45:43.041 --> 45:44.609
and this motherfucker's prints
are there too.

45:44.609 --> 45:46.778
This guy should put up a goddamn
billboard, Mike.

45:46.778 --> 45:48.346
I don't know.
I just know

45:48.346 --> 45:50.816
that I'm not gonna be able to
hide the fuckin' link on this.

45:50.816 --> 45:52.350
- Is it a secret there?

45:52.350 --> 45:54.419
- Yeah, it's common knowledge
and it's public knowledge.

45:54.419 --> 45:56.321
But if the state, feds, and the
fuckin' news pick up on this.

45:56.321 --> 45:57.722
Mike, I just need you
to make sure

45:57.722 --> 46:00.558
it just all stays with Mitch.
- Yep, yeah.

46:00.558 --> 46:02.027
- Mike, you don't
need to see it.

46:02.027 --> 46:03.461
All right.
You just don't need to see it.

46:03.461 --> 46:05.196
It's not gonna fuckin' do
anything for you.

46:05.196 --> 46:07.698
We got this fucker.
- I-I've gotta see it.

46:07.698 --> 46:09.467
- We got this guy,
SWAT's at his house right now.

46:09.467 --> 46:11.269
We're gonna fuckin' go there.
- It's my brother.

46:11.269 --> 46:12.938
I gotta see it.
Just let me see it.

46:12.938 --> 46:14.172
- All right,
don't touch anything.

46:14.172 --> 46:15.173
- Fine.
- Everybody's watchin' on this.

46:15.173 --> 46:17.775
- Fine.
- Let's make some room.

47:49.100 --> 47:51.369
- I mean, how else
could it end?

47:52.103 --> 47:53.905
For you too.

47:56.107 --> 47:58.743
When you help these parasites.

48:00.645 --> 48:03.581
You hold it together
for everyone else.

48:12.790 --> 48:15.426
It's fuckin' inevitable.

48:19.664 --> 48:22.833
Ya know, I always knew
that this would happen.

48:27.305 --> 48:30.441
I just thought
it would happen to you.

48:46.557 --> 48:48.626
- And so the United States Army

48:48.626 --> 48:51.262
moved the Cherokee further west.

48:51.262 --> 48:54.599
And this particular group,
some 1,600 people

48:54.599 --> 48:57.568
were pushed to a new home
in a territory

48:57.568 --> 49:00.738
that would become known
as Oklahoma.

49:01.806 --> 49:04.375
Upon reaching the banks
of the Mississippi

49:04.375 --> 49:07.145
where steamboats
would ferry them across,

49:07.145 --> 49:09.347
a dilemma arose.

49:09.347 --> 49:12.217
Every Cherokee family
keeps at least one dog,

49:12.217 --> 49:15.420
sometimes two or three
to aid in hunting,

49:15.420 --> 49:18.956
tracking game, protection,

49:18.956 --> 49:21.392
but to the Cherokee a dog

49:21.392 --> 49:24.529
is more than an aide
or a companion.

49:24.529 --> 49:29.367
It is a spirit helper,
an ancestor,

49:31.169 --> 49:33.338
a friend.

49:34.472 --> 49:37.175
Well, the ferry captains
wouldn't allow the dogs

49:37.175 --> 49:38.909
on board the boats,

49:38.909 --> 49:44.415
so, they pushed off,
leaving 3,000 dogs

49:44.415 --> 49:47.718
pacing the banks
of the Mississippi.

49:48.419 --> 49:50.888
When the boat
was a hundred yards out,

49:50.888 --> 49:53.324
almost in unison,

49:53.324 --> 49:56.694
the dogs began howling in agony.

49:57.128 --> 50:01.366
The Cherokees started crying,
calling to the captains.

50:01.366 --> 50:03.000
Turn back.

50:03.000 --> 50:08.439
The dogs hearing the pleas
of their families howled louder

50:08.439 --> 50:11.942
until one dog could stand
the separation no more

50:11.942 --> 50:14.345
and leapt into the river.

50:14.812 --> 50:18.883
Another dog followed
and another, and another.

50:18.883 --> 50:22.787
And soon 3,000 dogs
were churning the waters,

50:22.787 --> 50:27.692
fighting the current,
but the current was too strong.

50:27.692 --> 50:32.763
And one by one, they began
to disappear under the waters.

50:34.465 --> 50:36.934
Until there was
just one dog left.

50:37.902 --> 50:41.839
Strong, unwavering,

50:41.839 --> 50:46.877
the dog fought the current
and disappeared under the water

50:46.877 --> 50:49.814
and then reappeared
further downstream.

50:49.814 --> 50:55.019
The people screamed for him,
begging him to succeed.

50:56.954 --> 50:59.290
Until at last,

50:59.290 --> 51:02.627
too tired and no strength left,

51:02.627 --> 51:06.497
he disappeared into the waters
of the river.

51:06.497 --> 51:10.801
And the people
fell to their knees and wept.

51:17.508 --> 51:21.011
- Miriam, can I
have a word with you outside?

51:33.891 --> 51:35.960
- Aw, fuck.

51:38.263 --> 51:40.097
No.
- He in there?

51:40.097 --> 51:42.767
- Mike, you know how this works.
Come on, no way. No way.

51:42.767 --> 51:45.570
- Where is he? Come on.
I need this.

51:45.570 --> 51:48.072
Just give me this.
- Mike, it's not gonna happen.

51:48.072 --> 51:51.942
Mike, there's no way.
- It's for Mitch.

51:52.643 --> 51:54.078
- Mike, look, Mike.

51:54.078 --> 51:56.547
- If he goes to prison,
I can't fuckin' touch him.

51:56.547 --> 51:58.583
You understand that?
We don't work with the mafia.

51:58.583 --> 52:00.151
That fucker's gonna
sit in prison with his feet up

52:00.151 --> 52:03.188
for the rest of his fuckin' life
laughin' about this shit.

52:03.188 --> 52:04.622
- He won't.

52:04.622 --> 52:08.293
- Mike, I give you my word,
if he's alone in there,

52:08.293 --> 52:11.061
he will never
get off that couch.

52:11.629 --> 52:13.531
You hear me?
- Okay.

52:15.466 --> 52:16.667
- Don't worry, Mike.

52:16.667 --> 52:18.969
I do this shit for a livin',
brother.

52:19.970 --> 52:22.240
Come on boys, let's go.
- We got ya.

52:48.866 --> 52:52.603
- Here's what you will do.
Pick up the pistol.

52:54.439 --> 52:56.106
Do it.

52:56.674 --> 52:58.142
Come on, grab that gun.

52:58.142 --> 52:59.977
No, no, no, not by the barrel,
by the handle.

52:59.977 --> 53:02.680
You've seen too many movies,
Alberto.

53:03.281 --> 53:06.617
All right, good man.
Now point it toward the ceiling.

53:07.785 --> 53:09.454
Yeah.

53:09.787 --> 53:14.925
And bring the muzzle down
slowly in my direction.

53:22.933 --> 53:24.702
Thank you.

53:42.787 --> 53:46.724
- It went well.
The way you'd want it to go.

53:47.725 --> 53:49.927
He got to see it comin'.

53:51.296 --> 53:52.963
- Yeah.

54:25.296 --> 54:27.698
- How did this happen?

54:28.866 --> 54:31.336
- That's a really good question.

54:33.704 --> 54:36.341
- And who has the money?

54:36.874 --> 54:39.310
- The police.

54:39.877 --> 54:42.246
- Can you get it?

54:44.114 --> 54:45.816
- Nope.

54:49.019 --> 54:51.255
- That's going to be
a problem for you.

54:53.057 --> 54:54.725
- Son of a bitch.

54:59.664 --> 55:02.467
Now, listen to me.
They killed Milo's wife.

55:02.833 --> 55:04.369
They found the map.

55:04.369 --> 55:06.637
Then they killed
my fuckin' brother.

55:06.637 --> 55:09.807
Mitch was off limits.
And you know it.

55:09.807 --> 55:11.976
Everyone knew it.

55:12.309 --> 55:13.911
If Milo wants to blame us
for this shit,

55:13.911 --> 55:15.913
I'll have him killed in his cell
before midnight.

55:15.913 --> 55:18.215
Do you understand?

55:21.151 --> 55:23.421
Everything my brother gave you,

55:23.421 --> 55:26.256
I can take away in an afternoon.

55:26.256 --> 55:28.359
Don't ever threaten me again.

55:53.183 --> 55:54.952
Fuck!

1:00:03.067 --> 1:00:05.636
- Dawn.

1:00:07.404 --> 1:00:10.641
Have you ever once
come home before dawn?

1:00:15.179 --> 1:00:18.248
- Look, Ma, I don't-
- I don't either, Michael.

1:00:19.684 --> 1:00:22.219
What is there to say?

1:00:22.219 --> 1:00:24.588
He's gone.

1:00:25.489 --> 1:00:28.125
In the manner we all imagined.

1:00:31.595 --> 1:00:34.631
This will be your way, too,
you know?

1:00:34.631 --> 1:00:37.201
- Ma, we don't break the law.
You know that.

1:00:37.201 --> 1:00:39.336
We bend it.

1:00:39.336 --> 1:00:41.271
To make peace.

1:00:41.271 --> 1:00:43.708
For everybody.

1:00:43.708 --> 1:00:47.411
- I'm so familiar
with what you do.

1:00:47.411 --> 1:00:50.180
Your father invented it.

1:00:50.180 --> 1:00:53.150
But don't delude yourself
into thinking any of this

1:00:53.150 --> 1:00:55.853
is for the common good.

1:00:56.286 --> 1:00:59.757
You worked incredibly hard

1:00:59.757 --> 1:01:03.227
to accomplish
absolutely nothing.

1:01:03.227 --> 1:01:06.230
You prolonged the inevitable.

1:01:06.563 --> 1:01:11.135
Couriers, fix-it men,
part-time gangsters.

1:01:11.869 --> 1:01:13.303
And you think
because you don't

1:01:13.303 --> 1:01:17.641
make much money
that it's noble?

1:01:19.409 --> 1:01:24.614
Mitch, God rest his soul.
How I loved him.

1:01:25.816 --> 1:01:30.320
Was arrogant and lazy.
I know why he did it.

1:01:31.922 --> 1:01:35.459
For the attention, the power.

1:01:35.459 --> 1:01:37.795
But for the life of me,

1:01:37.795 --> 1:01:40.898
I'll never understand
why you do it.

1:01:41.932 --> 1:01:43.500
You hate it.

1:01:43.901 --> 1:01:47.637
You hate this town.
You have no friends.

1:01:48.672 --> 1:01:51.408
And all you've done
since you were a little boy

1:01:51.408 --> 1:01:54.078
is dream of leaving.

1:01:54.711 --> 1:01:57.915
And here you are.

1:01:58.615 --> 1:02:01.718
- What am I supposed to do, Ma?

1:02:04.221 --> 1:02:06.623
I don't know how to leave.

1:02:06.623 --> 1:02:12.029
- Michael, you just go.

1:02:57.607 --> 1:02:59.676
- Ugh.

1:03:29.706 --> 1:03:32.609
- Hi, I was hoping
you could help me.

1:03:32.609 --> 1:03:35.545
My daughter,
she's in the woman's prison

1:03:35.545 --> 1:03:37.647
and she wasn't...

1:03:37.647 --> 1:03:40.017
It doesn't matter.
She's in real trouble.

1:03:40.017 --> 1:03:41.551
I told her to
talk to the guards,

1:03:41.551 --> 1:03:43.954
but she said to come see you.

1:03:43.954 --> 1:03:46.924
- You got the wrong guy, ma'am.

1:03:46.924 --> 1:03:51.328
- Are you not the mayor?
- That was my brother.

1:03:52.897 --> 1:03:55.132
- I'm sorry to read that
in the newspaper.

1:03:55.132 --> 1:03:56.934
- Yeah, thank you.
Thank you.

1:03:56.934 --> 1:03:59.536
- My daughter,
she said to see you.

1:03:59.536 --> 1:04:01.171
She said that
you're the mayor now.

1:04:01.171 --> 1:04:04.408
- I'm sorry, but she's wrong.
She's wrong.

1:04:05.442 --> 1:04:07.844
- But, then what do I do?

1:04:07.844 --> 1:04:09.813
- I don't know.
- Sir,

1:04:09.813 --> 1:04:12.749
you don't understand, sir.
Please.

1:04:13.317 --> 1:04:15.652
I don't know
what they're gonna do to her.

1:04:16.053 --> 1:04:19.289
I don't know
what she will do to me.

1:04:21.992 --> 1:04:25.595
- Mike, this isn't for you.
Okay? Let's go.

1:04:26.063 --> 1:04:28.298
Let's go.
Come on, man.

1:04:31.168 --> 1:04:32.970
Mike.

1:04:41.245 --> 1:04:42.846
- What's her name?

1:04:57.361 --> 1:05:00.364
- MALE ANNOUNCER: Next time,
on "Mayor of Kingstown."

1:05:00.364 --> 1:05:02.432
- There's not one reason
for you to take this on.

1:05:02.432 --> 1:05:04.368
- MIKE:

1:05:04.368 --> 1:05:05.602
A lot of them.

1:05:05.602 --> 1:05:07.004
- Mitch wouldn't do
it that way, Mike.

1:05:07.004 --> 1:05:08.372
It's a big risk.

1:05:08.372 --> 1:05:09.673
- We had an arrangement
with your brother.

1:05:09.673 --> 1:05:11.441
We're here to decide if
you would be interested

1:05:11.441 --> 1:05:13.410
in being a paid informant.

1:05:13.410 --> 1:05:14.744
- Mike, where you at?

1:05:14.744 --> 1:05:16.613
You a friend of me or
are you friend of them?

1:05:18.748 --> 1:05:20.784
- I used to be friends
with Ian and his brother.

1:05:20.784 --> 1:05:24.054
Well, I guess Ian
sent someone else.

1:05:24.054 --> 1:05:25.322
Where is Iris?
